  Locus:
    Page: 117
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Ego
---
Nothing seems to happen exactly as its ego desires. It is simply the mind
clouded over by impure desires, and impervious to wisdom, which stubbornly
persists in thinking of “me” and “mine.”
